Darren Jones was standing for Bristol North West in a live TV debate . 
  He was seen stepping away from his podium after complaining of pins and needles in his legs . 
  The Labour candidate started swaying on his feet before collapsing in front of his opponents on Made in Bristol . 
  Mr Jones said he was suffering from a cold but was determined to take part in the debate . 
  The programme was delayed for nine minutes before going on air . 
 